      "body" : "This is implementation specific and may change at any time. There&#39;s no guarantee that the class has a no-arg constructor and even if it does have one that may do anything (perhaps <code>System.exit(0)</code>). I tend to write utility classes with a constructor as <code>private Void() { throw new Error(); }</code>. Some may prefer a no-value enum."
